Day 1 - Python Essentials & Time Complexity (Theory)

Topics Covered

- Lists (Mutable)
- Strings (Immutable)
- Sets
- Dictionaries
- Introduction to Time Complexity

Key Learnings

- Lists are mutable, meaning elements can be added, removed, or updated after creation.
- Strings are immutable; once created, they cannot be modified directly.
- Sets automatically remove duplicate values.
- Dictionaries store information using key-value pairs.
- O(1) represents constant time and is generally faster than O(n), which grows linearly with the input size.

